<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,152,327]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
The Israeli specimens have exactly the same characters as those described by Pilato, (1970, 1972) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Binda, M. G. &amp; Pilato, G." box="[151,413,189,215]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="47 - 60" refId="ref11393" refString="Binda, M. G. &amp; Pilato, G. (1972) Tardigradi muscicoli di Sicilia. IV Nota. Bollettino delle Sedute dell'Accademia Gioenia di Scienze naturali in Catania, Serie 4, 9, 47 - 60." type="journal article" year="1972">Binda &amp; Pilato (1972)</bibRefCitation>
for Italian specimens. They have lunules, a cuticular bar on the first three pairs of legs and the only supplementary gibbosities are between the main transverse gibbosities of: lines 3 and 4, lines 5 and 6, and lines 7 and 8.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,152,327]" box="[197,1406,301,327]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
This species, a new record for 
<collectingCountry box="[555,623,301,327]" name="Israel" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Israel</collectingCountry>
, is recorded for Europe, Northern America and Southern America.
</paragraph>
